<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Syrian, Lebanese Leaders Meet on Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Syrian President Hafez Al-Assad
met with his visiting Lebanese counterpart Elias Hrawi in
Latakia, Syria, today.
</P>
<P>
The two sides discussed the latest developments in the region
particularly the tense situation in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Hrawi arrived in the port city of Latakia overlooking the
Mediterranean Sea this moring for a state visit to Syria.
</P>
<P>
Syrian Foreign Minister Farouq Al-Shara attended the
Assad-Hrawi summit that was followed by a summit in camera,
according to the Syrian Arab News Agency (SANA).
</P>
<P>
However, SANA failed to give more details of the summit.
</P>
<P>
Hrawi's visit follows the escalation of tension in south
Lebanon. Israel committed another massacre against civilians
on August 18 when its military aircraft bombarded Saida city,
killing 9 civilians and wounding 43 others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
