<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seven Injured in Strike in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Seven persons were injured and
294 arrested during the strike which gripped the whole Nepal
today.
</P>
<P>
During the strike which was called by the Nepal Students Union,
a wing of the main opposition Nepali Congress, the demonstrators
damaged 16 vehicles including a government jeep being used by a
hospital and a drinking water tank, said a spokesman of the Home
Ministry.
</P>
<P>
A total of 294 persons, including 159 in the capital city of
Kathmandu, were arrested for trying to create disturbances,
disrupt transport services and vandalize public property, the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Police had to use tear gas to bring the situation under control
at Bardia district of mid-western Nepal.
</P>
<P>
Seven persons including two policemen and two local residents
were injured in sporadic incidents, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Almost all shops, schools and factories remained closed in
Kathmandu and vehicles remained off the streets throughout the
day.
</P>
<P>
Just five days ago, a strike called by political parties swept
the Kathmandu Valley, causing one injured and 59 detained.
</P>
<P>
More strikes will ensue as seven strikes have been set to be
organized in one month from August 19.  
</P>
</TEXT>
