<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng Praises ASEAN's Role in Regional Affairs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese Premier Li
Peng said today China attaches importance to the active role
played by the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) in
the regional affairs.
</P>
<P>
The enlargement of ASEAN conforms with the development trend of
global multi-polarization and is conducive to peace and
development in the Asia-Pacific region, Li Peng stated during his
talks with Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohammad here today.
</P>
<P>
"China supports ASEAN for its increasing role in the region,"
Li said when referring to the relationship between China and
ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
He said that in recent years, the relationship between China
and ASEAN enjoyed significant improvement with the mechanism of
dialogue and cooperation in full operation, moving into a stage of
stable and increasingly matured development.
</P>
<P>
"China is ready to work with ASEAN for establishing a
relationship of friendship and cooperation geared to the 21st
century," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier said that the meeting between leaders of
ASEAN and China, South Korea and Japan is a very good idea and it
is of great importance that the East Asian leaders get together to
look forward to the future and to exchange views on cooperation at
the time when the new century is approaching.
</P>
<P>
He said, "China is prepared to work closely with Malaysia for
the success of the meeting."
</P>
<P>
Mahathir thanked China for its active participation, saying
China's support is very important.
</P>
<P>
Both Li and Mahathir noted that the main feature of the current
world situation is that the world is accelerating the development
of multi-polarization, which they said is conducive to peace and
stability in the region and the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said that the days when one or two countries dominate
the world has gone forever and in such a situation, various forces
and countries in the world should strengthen consultation and
coordination for this is conducive to resist hegemonism.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng agreed with Mahathir on this point.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders also discussed other regional and international
issues of common interest.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng invited Mahathir to visit China again at his
convenience and Mahathir expressed his thanks for the invitation.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir has paid four visits to China since 1985 with the
latest one last year.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng arrived here on August 21 for a four-day official visit
to Malaysia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
