<HEADLINE> China Promotes Art Education in Primary, Middle Schools </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Li Lanqing, member of the
Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party
of China, today called on art and music teachers in primary and
middle schools nationwide to improve the country's art education.
</P>
<P>
Li, who is also vice-premier of the State Council, attended a
meeting here to award 500 outstanding music and art teachers, who
were selected from among 296,668 art educators in some 200,000
primary and middle schools across the country.
</P>
<P>
He said that the importance of art education has been attached
by the governments at all levels, and the role of art teachers has
become increasingly important.
</P>
<P>
China has changed its previous practice of "teaching for exams"
into a comprehensive, quality education system in recent years, he
said.
</P>
<P>
To further develop art education and train the teachers, the
Art Education Commission under the State Education Commission
(SEC) set up a lecture group made up of well-known experts in the
field of art education, said a SEC official at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The experts in the group will host a series of talks to help
provide further instruction for art teachers in primary and middle
schools.  
</P>
</TEXT>
