<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uruguay Defeats Mexico to Top Group A </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Host Uruguay stormed back
from an early deficit to clinch an 81-67 victory over Mexico in
group A of the America basketball tournament here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Oscar Castellanos' 17 points put Mexico to an early lead. But
the host boosted by a partisan crowd to take it over and build a
first-half advantage of 40-34.
</P>
<P>
Uruguay than dominated the second half en route to beat their
rivals by a winning margin of 14 points.
</P>
<P>
Gustavo Szczygielski scored a game high 25 points to rally
Uruguay to the top of Group A in the tournament, which is a
qualifying event for the 1998 World Championship in Greece.
</P>
<P>
In Thursday's other games, Puerto Rico edged the Dominican
Republic 88-85, while Argentina trounced Cuba 81-73, and Venezuela
defeated the United States 85-75.
</P>
<P>
The United States, who have not sent their best line-ups to the
current tournament, will defend their champion in Greece. The top
four from the other nine teams will also qualify for the 1998
championship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
