<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets Malaysian Head of State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Supreme Head of
State Tuanku Ja'afar met with visiting Chinese Premier Li Peng and
his wife Zhu Lin at the Royal Palace here this evening.
</P>
<P>
Extending a warm welcome to Li on his official visit here,
Ja'afar said Li had fruitful talks with Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohammad, and made a very good speech at the welcome
meeting organized by the Institute of Diplomatic and Foreign
Relations, where he also answered questions raised by
participants.
</P>
<P>
Li's visit would serve to promote a in-depth advancement of the
Malaysia-China friendly relations of cooperation, Ja'afar added.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that he visited China in July this year as guest of
Chinese President Jiang Zemin and saw with his own eyes the great
changes that had taken place in China since the reform and opening
up.
</P>
<P>
This had left him a deep impression, Ja'afar said.
</P>
<P>
Li stated that Ja'afar's recent visit to China was very
successful and he was very pleased to visit Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
"The frequent exchange of visits between leaders of the two
countries is of great importance to increase mutual understanding
and promote the furtherance of the bilateral relations," the
premier said.
</P>
<P>
He elaborated that he had a friendly and cordial talk with
Mahathir and exchanged in-depth views on many important issues and
achieved complete consensus.
</P>
<P>
Both sides are satisfied with the stable and healthy progress
of the bilateral ties, and are willing to further tighten the
exchanges and cooperation in various fields, and to continue to
maintain the high-level exchange of visits, Li stated.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that both countries would also work to promote the
bilateral economic and trade cooperation and strengthen their
coordination on regional and international issues.
</P>
<P>
"We believe, through joint efforts, the good-neighborly
relations will score great achievements," the premier said.
</P>
<P>
Li conveyed the best regards from President Jiang Zemin to
Ja'afar, who asked Li to pass his best wishes to Jiang upon his
return home.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Ja'afar and his wife hosted a dinner for Li
and his wife Zhu Lin.
</P>
<P>
Present at the dinner included main members of Li's entourage.
</P>
<P>
Li is scheduled to visit the Pulau Penang tomorrow.  
</P>
</TEXT>
