<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Urges More Efforts for Tourism Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwean government is
seriously looking into the possibilities of establishing a
tourism venture fund to allow more blacks to enter the lucrative
industry, a deputy minister said here today.
</P>
<P>
Mines, Environment and Tourism Deputy Minister Edward
Chindori-Chininga said there is potential for tourism development
in Zimbabwe which went untapped due to lack of finance and
"entrepreneurial creativity".
</P>
<P>
"My ministry has submitted proposals for such a venture fund
mechanism to a number of financial institutions which are working
with us in this effort," he said.
</P>
<P>
"This thinking comes as a result of the realization that the
local financial supporting environment is not friendly to the
extend that the indigenous persons in particular cannot start
business in the tourism sector and survive," he said.
</P>
<P>
He was speaking at a one-day preparatory workshop for the
Southern African Development Community Regional Tourism Investors
Forum to be held in Harare from October 28-30.
</P>
<P>
He urged the public and private sector to ensure success of
the conference through logistical support. 
</P>
</TEXT>
