<DOCNO> XIE19970823.0026 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over 100 Tutsi Refugees Killed in Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Over 107 refugees have been
massacred and 30 others wounded in a raid on a camp housing
ethnic Tutsis from former Zaire in Gisenyi, a town at Rwanda's
northwestern border, the U.N. refugee agency said today.
</P>
<P>
Pamela O'toole, spokeswoman of the U.N. High Commissioner for
Refugees (UNCHR) said preliminary reports showed that the ethnic
Tutsis, who fled fighting in the Masisi region of the former
Zaire, were slaughtered with machetes by unidentified attackers
late on Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
"This is shocking and extremely worrying," O'toole said.
</P>
<P>
Rwandan government officials put the death toll higher at 120
including local civilians in the area, she said.
</P>
<P>
O'toole said the massacre at Mudende camp near the border town
of gisenyi, was reported to the UNCHR by Adventist Relief, an aid
agency working in the camp in the early hours today.
</P>
<P>
Some 8,000 remaining ethnic Tutsi refugees fled the camp after
the attack, she said.
</P>
<P>
Aid workers said Rwandan troops today began a hot-pursuit of
rebels in the mountainous region, where more than 2,000 Hutus
have been killed by the army in recent months in
cordon-and-search operations, according to the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The attack is the latest in the bloody ethnic Hutu-Tutsi war
in Africa's troubled Great Lakes region, which aid officials say
is far from over.
</P>
<P>
Hutus, the majority tribe in Rwanda, massacred more than half
a million minority Tutsis and Hutu moderates in 1994. Many fled
to Zaire, now renamed the Democratic Republic of Congo, when the
Hutu government was toppled after minority Tutsis swept to power.
</P>
<P>
The victims were part of some 15,000 ethnic Tutsis from the
Masisi region who returned to Rwanda in 1995 and 1996 because of
fighting between Hutus and Tutsis as well as other indigenous
local tribes in the hilly area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
