<HEADLINE> Fighting Continues in Northern Brazzaville </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Troops loyal to Congolese
President Pascal Lissouba have intensified attacks on the central
and northern parts of Brazzaville held by the militiamen of
former president Sassou Nguesso.
</P>
<P>
Congo's government radio reported today that several
rival-held districts in the capital have fallen to Lissouba's
soldiers, which Sassou has dismissed the claim as a lie.
</P>
<P>
The report said that Sassou's home is said to be stricken by
shells.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this week, the government radio claimed that
Lissouba's forces had located Sassou's hideout in the capital and
warned that he can either surrender or get himself killed.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the government has denied reports of the fallen
Ouesso - the largest northern city in the country to Sassou's
supporters. Sassou insists that he still holds it.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of people have died since fighting broke out in
Brazzaville between forces loyal to President Lissouba and the
rival militia of former president Sassou.
</P>
<P>
Sassou has accused Lissouba of looking for every means to
maintain in power. Lissouba has denied the accusation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
