<HEADLINE> China's Role Key in Global Environmental </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 22 (Xinhua) -- China has made considerable
contributions to and played a "cooperative and productive role"
in world environmental affairs, said U.N. Environmental Program
(UNEP) Executive Director Elizabeth Dowdeswell today.
</P>
<P>
"China is involved in making contribution in almost every
global issue, such as ozone protection, or climate change... At
all major international, global environmental discussions, China
is there," she said in an interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
China's reaction to key challenges facing the earth such as
ozone reduction and climate change is particularly important for
the whole world, said Dowdeswell, who has visited China almost
once a year since 1992.
</P>
<P>
China is always ready and willing to share experience and
information with other countries on environmental issues, she
said, adding China is the most supportive nation for
Nairobi-based UNEP, the sole U.N. body with headquarters in the
third world.
</P>
<P>
Dowdeswell also spoke highly of the Chinese government for its
great efforts to draft and implement environmental laws and
spread environmental protection knowledge around the country
through education systems and mass media.
</P>
<P>
"The (Chinese) government is on the right track. I think it is
taking environment issues very seriously," she said.
</P>
<P>
"In the last ten years, China has been most successful in
ensuring that environmental protection is built into governmental
policy-making... at the highest-level," she noted.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, she said that China faces a main challenge to
maintain rapid economic growth and sound environment at the same
time since it holds a huge population. 
</P>
</TEXT>
