<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN Agencies Discuss Disaster Management Training </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Representatives of the UN
Department of Humanitarian Affairs and the UNDP held consultations
this week in New York on the second phase of the Disaster
Management Training Program, a jointly managed project created in
1990, according to a UN news release.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of this program is to deliver training to national
government officials, UN country agencies, donors and
non-governmental organizations in order to strengthen and develop
their capacities for the management of complex emergencies and
natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
The program is specifically designed for each state in close
cooperation with the resident coordinator and the respective
in-country disaster management team.
</P>
<P>
Activities have already started in Armenia, Azerbaijan,
Georgia, Angola and Mozambique. The next target countries are
Sudan, Yemen, Djibouti and the Palestinian territories. 
</P>
</TEXT>
