<HEADLINE> SINOTASHIP Celebrates 30th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese-Tanzanian
Joint Shipping Company (SINOTASHIP) held a ceremony here this
evening to mark the company's 30th founding anniversary.
</P>
<P>
Among over 100 guests invited to the ceremony were Chinese
Minister of Communications Huang Zhendong and Tanzanian Minister
for Communications and Transport William Kusila.
</P>
<P>
In their toasts, the two ministers reviewed the achievements
SINOTASHIP has achieved in the past 30 years and expressed the
wish that the company will make further progress which will
benefit developments in both Tanzania and China.
</P>
<P>
SINOTASHIP was found as a joint Chinese-Tanzanian venture by
the Chinese and Tanzanian governments on June 22, 1967 at the
initiative of former President Junius Nyerere of Tanzania and the
late Premier Zhou Enlai of China.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture is based on the principles of friendship,
cooperation, equality and mutual benefit. The main objective of
SINOTASHIP was and still is to provide a maritime transportation
service for the trade between China and Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, the company's vessels had carried
4.42 million tons of cargo, mostly imports and exports between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Ever since its formation in 1967, SINOTASHIP has made profits
totaling more than 21 million U.S. Dollars from shipping
operations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
