<HEADLINE> VAT System Also to Be Introduced in Zanzibar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Value Added Tax (VAT)
will also be introduced in Zanzibar, Tanzanian Minister for
Finance Daniel Yona told the National Assembly in Dodoma in
central Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Winding up a debate on the VAT Bill shortly before it was
endorsed by the house, Yona said that the Isles government has
agreed to adopt the TAX.
</P>
<P>
"The Isles government has in principle agreed to adopt VAT and
the Tanzania Revenue Authority (TRA) will provide the necessary
technical assistance in preparations for the scheme," Yona said.
</P>
<P>
The finance minister, however, said that VAT was not a union
matter, thus the TAX would be applied in accordance with Zanzibar
laws.
</P>
<P>
He said VAT would have a single tariff fixed at 20 percent and
would be imposed on traders with an annual turn of over 20
million Tanzanian Shillings (about 33,000 U.S. Dollars).
</P>
<P>
The minister said initially about 10,000 such traders were
expected to be registered in the Mainland.
</P>
<P>
The VAT will be introduced in the Mainland July 1, 1998.
</P>
</TEXT>
