<HEADLINE> Hungary Wins Womens' Individual Epee Title at Universiade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Timea Nagy of Hungary won
her country the first gold medal at the 19th World University Games
here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Nagy beat her Russian rival Karina Aznavourian 15-13 in the final
to win the title of the women's individual epee, the second gold of
the Universiade fencing tournament.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, twice world champion Samuel Tucker of Cuba took the
men's individual foil title.
</P>
<P>
World fencing powerhouse Italy failed for the second consecutive
day to win a medal in fencing tournament.
</P>
<P>
The final was an exciting one with Nagy a slight better than her
opponent. But Aznavourian never gave up and put up some brilliant
performances.
</P>
<P>
Victoria Titova of Ukraine and Barbara Ciszewska of Poland shared
the bronze medal after losing to Nagy and Aznavourian in the
semi-finals respectively.
</P>
<P>
Monkia Maciewska of Poland finished fifth, followed by Yang Shaoqi
of China in the sixth place.
</P>
<P>
Guo Ying, coach of the Chinese fencing team, said that he was
satisfied with the performance of Yang Shaoqi.
</P>
<P>
"Yang Shaoqi did good today. Her problem is that she is not strong
enough and can not follow the pace of her opponent." Guo Ying said.
</P>
<P>
The level of the women's individual epee competitions is very high
as the gold medalist and runner-up of last month's world championships
at Cape Town were all eliminated before the quarter-finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
