<HEADLINE> Russia Grabs Women's Gymnastics Team Gold at Universiade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Italy, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Russia grabbed the gold medal
in the women's gymnastics team competition of the 19th World
University Games at the Sports Center here on Friday evening.
</P>
<P>
The Russian team collected a total of 110.537 points in the floor,
beams, uneven bars and vault events.
</P>
<P>
The United States took the silver medal with 108.986 points while
the Japanese team came third with 108.624 points.
</P>
<P>
The fourth to Sixth places went to China, Ukraine and South Korea.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 gymnasts from 10 countries and regions competed in the
women's team competitions.
</P>
<P>
China won the men's team gold on the opening day of Universiade
gymnastics tournament on thursday.
</P>
<P>
In today's individual rhythmic gymnastic competition, Bulgairan
Tatiana Ogryzko and Ukrainean Elena Vitrichenko shared the lead with
an identical score of 19.749 points, followed by Eva Serrano of France
with 19.649 points after two events.
</P>
<P>
The rhythmic gymnastic competition will produce a gold medal for
the individual all-around event on Saturday and on the same day
gymnasts will vie for the men's and women's individual all-around
titles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
