<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Football Team Lose But Still Advance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese football team lost
to their American counterparts 3-1 in the last group match but still
qualified for the second round at the Universiade here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, having been ensured of a berth in the second
round, didn't play the match up to their level while the American team
went all out for a win.
</P>
<P>
Their efforts paid off as Johnny Torres scored a goal while
Benjamin Olsen added two. Qiu Zhonghui of China narrowed the gap to
1-3 in the second half.
</P>
<P>
The victory put the American team on top of group D with seven
points. China finished second with six points from two wins against
one loss.
</P>
<P>
Top two teams from each group qualify for the second round.
</P>
<P>
Hosts Italy beat Britain 3-1 to advance into the second round.
Fanesi Massimiliano opened the scoring for the host team at the 12th
minute. Coates Marc of Britain levelled the score 1-1 at the 18th
mark.
</P>
<P>
In the second half, Gianni Califano and Luca Ulivi each scored once
to give Italy a 3-1 victory and a ticket to the second round.
</P>
<P>
Brazil also qualified to the second round from group A after
beating Iran 5-1 on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands and South Korea emerged as the two qualifiers from
group C as the two teams played to a 1-1 draw in their last group
match on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The draw gave the two teams one point each and they qualified with
an identical total of five points, one point more than Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
In group B, Japan drew Ukraine 0-0 while Ireland beat Morocco 3-1.
Ukraine qualified as the winners of the group with 5 points. Ireland
also advanced to the second round with four points as they had a
better goal difference than the Japanese team. 
</P>
</TEXT>
