<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Rebound From Daily Plunge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 22 (Xinhua) -- New York stocks staged a
stunning rebound today, erasing almost all of a 177-point plunge
by the Dow Jones industrial average.
</P>
<P>
The Dow, down nearly 125 points with just half an hour left to
the session, roared back to close at 7,887.91, down only 6.04
points, finishing the week with a gain of 193.25 points.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues still outnumbered advancers by a 2-to-1 margin
on the New York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 457.59
million shares as against 497.57 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators also rallied into the close. The
technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index recovered about
three-quarters of an early 2 percent plunge.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list, down nearly 20 points at
its low, fell just 1.51 to 923.54.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index fell 8.67 to 1,598.69, the NYSE
composite index fell 0.83 to 478.93, and the American Stock
Exchange composite index fell 2.73 to 643.83. points.
</P>
<P>
The Dow had swung at least 100 points in each of the last five
sessions, losing 247 points last Friday, gaining 323 over the next
three sessions, and then sliding 127 points Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Stocks were pressured by another weak day in the bond market,
which was weighed down by a sharp drop in the dollar's value on
foreign exchange markets.
</P>
<P>
As bond prices fell, the yield on the 30-year Treasury rose as
high as 6.68 percent, up from 6.62 percent late Thursday and 6.54
percent late Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
