<HEADLINE> Russian, Finnish Premiers Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin and his Finnish counterpart Paavo Lipponen met today
in Russia's northwestern republic of Karelia, which is bounded by
Finland, said a report from the republic's town of Kostomuksha.
</P>
<P>
Russia greatly appreciates Finland's stance on dealing with
many European political issues including enlargement of NATO and
the European Union, Chernomyrdin said after the meeting.
</P>
<P>
