role in solving the problem of the status of Russian-speaking
people in the Baltic states through its special ties with Estonia.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin hopes to "open more border passages" between the
two countries to promote development of their relations.
</P>
<P>
A check point with 10 lanes was recently opened on the
Russian-Finnish border. It is capable of handling 500 vehicles
and 1,500 passengers a day, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Another check point is scheduled to be opened on the
Russian-Finnish border during the first half of 1998, said Anatoly
Kruglov, chairman of the Russian State Customs Committee, who is
accompanying Chernomyrdin.
</P>
<P>
Lipponen, who arrived at Kostomuksha on Friday, said he was
satisfied with both economic and political talks with
Chernomyrdin. 
</P>
