<HEADLINE> Chiluba Not to Seek Re-election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Zambian President Frederick
Chiluba said today that he will not seek re-election in the next
poll in the year 2001.
</P>
<P>
He made the statement in Indonesia, where he is having a
three-day visit.
</P>
<P>
The Zambia News Agency quoted him as saying "No, No, No," in
response to a question on whether he will run for office for a
third time.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba said that he consider himself a pioneer of change and
dismissed the motion held in some quarters that leaders in the
third world hang on to power for too long.
</P>
<P>
Under the constitution amendment bill adopted last year, the
country's president cannot run for a third time but some people
expressed doubt recently asking why if he is supported by his
countrymen.
</P>
<P>
Referring to his visits to Singapore and Indonesia, Chiluba
said the aim of his tour is to promote economic and technical
cooperation with these countries. 
</P>
