the "national dialog" last Wednesday with militant groups
including Hams, which has claimed responsibility for several
deadly attacks on Israeli civilians.
</P>
<P>
"The various Palestinian forces with their varied orientations
reiterated their support to Yasser Arafat," said the PLO official.
</P>
<P>
"They also underlined the importance of maintaining Palestinian
unity to face the deteriorating situation resulting from the
Israeli siege imposed on the Palestinian people, he added.
</P>
<P>
