Palestinian areas after the July 30 suicide bombings in a
Jerusalem market place, and demanded Arafat to crack down on
extremists.
</P>
<P>
Agha condemned the Israeli and American criticisms launched
against the PNA as aimed at weakening the position of Arafat and
called upon Washington to be more serious to salvage the
peace march.
</P>
<P>
"The recent visit paid by U.S. Mideast Peace Coordinator Dennis
Ross to the region took only into consideration the Israeli
security interests while ignoring the Palestinian needs," he
added.
</P>
<P>
The American mediator helped repair the Palestinian-Israeli
security coordination system but did not revive peace talks during
his renewed shuttle diplomacy in the region early this month.
