<HEADLINE> Australian Agricultural Area Suffers from Drought </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The drought was tightening its
grip on New South Wales (NSW), a major agricultural area of the
country, with 63 percent of the state now officially drought
declared, a news release said today.
</P>
<P>
The drought figure was up from 50 percent declared last month.
</P>
<P>
The Bureau of Meteorology has predicted the below-average
rainfall was unlikely to improve and prolonged dry spells have
been forecast.
</P>
<P>
NSW agriculture Minister Richard Amery has conceded the state
was about to enter a period of extended drought.
</P>
<P>
He said, crop outlooks in the central and southern slopes were
now on a "knife edge".
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said, most of the northeastern part in
Australia is under the impact of El Nino which would lead to a
slump in crop yields and production, accounting for a fall of
almost 1.35 billion US dollars in crop values.  
</P>
