<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti Minister Leaves for Turkey for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti Minister of
Commerce and Industry Jassem Al-Mudhaf left for Turkey today on a
four-day visit to hold talks with Turkish officials on ways of
promoting commercial exchanges between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The minister will hold talks with his Turkish counterpart
Yalim Erez and other officials on sidelines of the four-day Izmir
International Exhibition which will open Sunday in Turkey, the
Kuwait News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
"Historic and distinctive ties binding Kuwait and Turkey have
facilitated exportation of Turkish products to Kuwait," the
minister said.
</P>
<P>
But so far there is no organized navigation lines between the
two countries and some customs technical problems exist, he
indicated.
</P>
<P>
A Kuwaiti-Turkish committee meets once a year to assess
commercial exchanges and tackle problems hampering cooperation
between the two countries' businessmen.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral trade volume amounted to some 150 million U.S.
dollars in 1996 in Turkish favor.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait and Turkey signed several accords over the past two
decades, including an agreement for transit, transfer of
passengers and commodities in 1970, an agreement for
encouragement and protection of investments in 1988, a deal for
industrial, economic and technical cooperation in 1992 and an
agreement on avoiding double taxation in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
