<DOCNO> XIE19970823.0106 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Large Jadeware Market in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- A visit to the Kunming World
Trade Center and its 1,500 stalls, where the fifth export trade
fair is underway, can be a dazzling affair.
</P>
<P>
About 300 of the stalls are for jadeware produced locally and
as well as from Thailand, Burma, Malaysia, and Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Judging jade, because it is sometimes a luxury, can be
difficult. A pair of jade bracelets sold by local jewellers can
cost thousands of yuan, while similar products can be bought at a
rather low price from a Burmese dealer.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan and Burma account for a large part of the jewelry
exhibition. One jewellery from Burma says that he earned over
100,000 yuan in one day.
</P>
<P>
A Yunnan jadeware market is taking shape. The province has two
advantages in this business. One is that, in addition to its own
abundant jade resources, it borders Southeast and South Asia,
which are famous for their jade products. The other is that Yunnan
has a long history of dealing with jade. Jadeware occupies a major
part of Yunnan's tourist trade.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
