<DOCNO> XIE19970823.0107 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Credit Cooperatives Reduce Risks in Guizhou Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, August 23 (Xinhua) -- China's deep-going financial
reform has proved successful in southwestern Guizhou Province, as
both financial risks and the ratio of non-performing loans of the
rural credit cooperatives have decreased substantially.
</P>
<P>
The rural credit cooperatives have turned for the better since
financial reform in the countryside was launched, a provincial
banking official said.
</P>
<P>
The cooperatives' proportions of both deposits and loans in the
provincial banking system have gone up in recent years, reversing
a downward trend since 1988.
</P>
<P>
During the period from January to June this year, the number of
credit cooperatives deemed highly risky declined by 85 while the
proportion of non-performing loans edged down by 1.51 percentage
points.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970823.0108 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Largest Port City in Grip of Loadshedding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The erratic power supply coupled
with loadshedding hit Chittagong city, the biggest port city of
Bangladesh, over the past week, seriously affecting the production
and normal life, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The port city now receives supply of only 35 megawatt of
electricity as against its minimum requirement of 170 megawatt a
day, according to the Power Development Board (PDB).
</P>
<P>
The extreme poor state of power supply has again put the port
city dwellers in sufferings beyond all bounds. Hardly an area of
the port city now goes without experiencing power failure a day.
Even at night, the dwellers experience power failures and
loadshedding several times.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the fluctuation of voltage is also now worse than
ever before and the low-voltage too has reached all time high.
</P>
<P>
The unprecedented loadshedding has seriously affected the
production of over 4,000 mills and industries of the port city.
</P>
<P>
With the present pace of development of the city, the demand
for the supply of electricity is fast going up. It is informed
that Chittagong city needs the supply of more than 250 megawatt
electricity a day.
</P>
<P>
Compared to that necessity, the PDB is used to supply there 70
to 100 megawatt a day during the normal period, the local press
reported.
</P>
<P>
The PDB attributed the loadshedding to the poor generation of
electricity at three power plants in the Chittagong area, which
significantly shrunk over the past one week following the cut down
of supply of gas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
