<HEADLINE> Liuzhou New High Technology Development Zone Taking Shape </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The new high technology
development zone in Liuzhou, the largest industrial city in
southwestern China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, has
experienced rapid development.
</P>
<P>
The zone now has 135 enterprises, which have registered a total
income of slightly over 1.83 billion yuan. These enterprises are
engaged in wide-ranging industries, including computer information
processing, new materials, laser technology, and refined chemistry.
</P>
<P>
The introduction of a new management mode helped to raise the
zone's total earnings by 223 percent to 333 million yuan for the
first six months of the year, with its industrial output value
rising by 303 percent to 363 million yuan, and sales volume by 236
percent to 330 million yuan.
