<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sanlian Group Expands Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The Sanlian Group in east China's
Shandong Province plans a vigorous business expansion in line with
actual conditions in China.
</P>
<P>
Sanlian President Zhang Jisheng said that the group's plans
through the turn of the century call for the establishment of a
comprehensive organizational structure based on trade, banking,
information, chain stores, catering service, tourism and
industrial production.
</P>
<P>
The Sanlian Group, one of Shandong's eight largest company
groups engaged in commerce and trade, has total assets of over 2.1
billion yuan, with annual turnover of 1.85 billion yuan and pretax
profits of 78 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The group expects that by the year 2000, its total assets will
reach five billion yuan, its assets to debt ratio will be less
than 50 percent, and its business volume will amount to 13 billion
yuan with 950 million of pretax profits and export earning of 100
million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The group has drafted a plan to adopt acquisitions and joint
development as a means of reaching its goal. The Sanlian group
plans to expand its business to Beijing, Shanghai and other
provincial capitals. It will also continue to import advanced
technology from foreign countries and will intensify technical
renovations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
