<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Earns Remittances of 782 Million Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh earned 34.8 billion
taka (about 782 million U.S. dollars) as remittances from overseas
laborers during the first six months of this year, said official
statistics.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ministry for Labor and Manpower, the total
earnings in this sector in 1996 were 56.85 billion taka (about
1.28 billion dollars), which accounted for 41 percent of the total
foreign exchange earnings of the country for the same period.
</P>
<P>
During the first half of this year, a total of 125,056 persons
were sent officially to different countries. They include 2,330
professionals, 38,337 skilled, 22,713 semi-skilled and 61,676
unskilled people.
</P>
<P>
The ministry had a target of exporting 205,200 people as
overseas laborers.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his satisfaction over the growing demands for
Bangladeshi manpower abroad, a high-ranking official from the
ministry said that the government is exploring new avenues to
expand manpower export.
</P>
<P>
Besides some Middle East and Southeast Asian countries, Russia,
Australia and some African countries have also shown positive
interest in recruiting manpower from Bangladesh, said the
official.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the government is keen to send skilled persons
instead of unskilled ones. It would help fetch maximum remittances
as well as enhance the country's image abroad, he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
