<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Expanded Product Line for Convenience Stores </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Central government authorities
recently decided to permit fast-growing neighborhood convenience
store chains to expand their product lines.
</P>
<P>
In addition to main products such as foodstuffs and daily-use
items, the outlets will be permitted to sell books, newspapers,
stamps, envelopes and video products. They will also be allowed to
offer public telephone services.
</P>
<P>
A joint circular issued by the State Economic and Trade
Committee and the Ministry of Internal Trade calls for local
authorities to approve applications for expanded product
lines. The goal is to provide greater service to the general
public.
</P>
<P>
According to the circular, tobacco monopoly authorities across
the country can also select chain stores for trial sales of
cigarettes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
