<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Airport Police Successful in Fighting Crime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Airport police across China, in
a campaign against the increasing amount of crime, seized over
360,000 illegal publications, and video and audio products.
</P>
<P>
These included over 27,000 pornographic works.
</P>
<P>
In 15 of the most serious cases, public security officers at
Guangzhou's Baiyun Airport discovered 183,000 pirated VCDs, 7,085
of them with pornographic content, on December 9 last year.
</P>
<P>
On May 15, the Hainan branch of a Hongkong-based air shipper
managed to ship 7,000 pirated VCD cassettes to Guangzhou where
they were stopped by public security officer. Based on this
information, an underground producer of VCDs was uncovered and
over 110,000 pirated VCDs seized.
</P>
<P>
In one raid public security officers of the Anhui Provincial
Civil Aviation Administration seized 7,970 VCDs, 354 of which had
pornographic contents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
