<HEADLINE> 3 More Foreign Banks to Start Operation in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Three more foreign banks will be
given permission soon for doing business in Bangladesh to
supplement the activities of the banks in the country's financial
sector, informed sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
According the sources, three leading banks, one each from
Germany, Japan and Denmark, have sought permission to start
operation in Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh Bank has already given them green signal that the
necessary permission will be given by this month.
</P>
<P>
At present, a total of 13 foreign banks are doing business in
Bangladesh. Those banks are from Australian, Britain, Pakistan,
India and the United States.
</P>
<P>
The major operations of the foreign banks so far were
restricted to only trade financing. But, in the wake of the
serious liquidity crisis faced by the local commercial banks in
extending term loans, the government has withdrawn the
restrictions.
</P>
<P>
The foreign banks have also expressed their willingness to
expand their lending to the fund-starved industrial sector,
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The foreign banks are now examining the feasibility of
industrial financing and a proposal to this effect will be
submitted to the Finance Ministry at the end of this month,
sources informed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
