<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Western Scholars Criticize Wolf's Remarks as "Absolutely nonsense" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Leading Western scholars on
Tibetan studies expressed their "shock" at US congressman Frank
Wolf's remarks that "Tibetan language and culture are being
destroyed" and criticized him as being "arrogant and ignorant."
</P>
<P>
Republican Representative Frank Wolf, who recently sneaked into
Tibet in the disguise as a tourist, sensationally announced on
Wednesday that during his four-day tour to Tibet he saw that the
region was being "swallowed" by China through mass arrests and
brutal repression and Tibetan language and culture are being
destroyed.
</P>
<P>
He called on the West to "take urgent action to save" the
Himalayan Buddhist culture.
</P>
<P>
Researchers from the United Sates, Britain, Australia and
Germany attending the ongoing '97 Beijing Seminar on Tibetan
Studies refuted Wolf's arguments by citing their own
experience. Tibetan traditional culture is flourishing, they said.
</P>
<P>
"Wolf's remarks are nonsense. It's absolutely nonsense. He must
be blind," said Professor Colin Mackerras, a professor of
Tibetology of Griffith University and chairman of the Modern Asian
Studies School in Australia.
</P>
<P>
"He seems to know everything, but his remarks obviously show
that he knows nothing of the Tibetan culture and obviously he has
never been to Tibetan rural areas," Professor Mackerras said.
</P>
<P>
Professor Mackerras, who has made five visits to the Tibet
Autonomous Region as well as the Tibetan areas of Qinghai, Gansu
and Sichuan provinces, said that "Tibetan culture is stronger than
ever before."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
