<HEADLINE> DPRK Chides Remarks by Japanese Officials on China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The official daily newspaper
Minju Choson in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK)
today carried a commentary, criticizing the remarks by some
Japanese government officials that violate China's sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
The commentary said that the remarks that Japan-U.S. defense
cooperation guidelines would cover the Taiwan Straits has
triggered strong condemnation from China, and is something China
would never tolerate.
</P>
<P>
During World War II, Japanese invaders in China had inflicted
severe sufferings on the Chinese people, and many of their
atrocities were beyond imagination, it said.
</P>
<P>
Some people in Japan want to distort the past crimes, and seek
militarism in the future, and this has alerted not only the
Chinese people but people all over Aisa, it added.
</P>
<P>
On August 17, Japanese Chief Cabinet Secretary Seiroku Kajiyama
said that the new Japanese-U.S. guideline would cover the Taiwan
Straits.
</P>
<P>
His remarks were later confirmed by a series of senior
government officials in Japan, including Foreign Minister Yukihiko
Ikeda who said the remarks were in line with the consistent
position of the Japanese government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
