<HEADLINE> Huge Gold Dust Seized by Police in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 23 (Xinhua) -- About six tons of gold
dust were seized by police on Friday in a hostel in Welkom, Free
State province of South Africa.
</P>
<P>
A combined force of police and soldiers, assisted by security
officers from local gold mines, took part in the raid at 1:30
a.m., today's local newspapers quoted a police spokesman as
saying.
</P>
<P>
About 3,000 residents of the hostel had a rude awakening when
rooms and living quarters were searched for weapons, stolen goods
and drugs.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the massive gold dust haul, a large stock of
equipment used in refining gold dust was also confiscated. The
crime blitz also yielded 62 kilogram of dagga.
</P>
<P>
More than 250 illegal foreign aliens were arrested during the
raid, the spokesman said, adding stolen electronic goods, foreign
bank notes and ammunition were also confiscated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
