<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Death toll Rises in Northern Philippine floods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The death toll resulting from
this week's flooding in Central Luzon, the Northern Philippines,
rose to 21, the Department of Social Welfare and Development said
today.
</P>
<P>
The regional office of the Department of Social Welfare and
Development today released the list of casualties of the massive
floods in Central Luzon.
</P>
<P>
The office said that six persons were buried alive by landslide
in Subic, and the other fatalities include six in Pampanga, three
in Bataan, four in Bulacan and two in Olongapo city.
</P>
<P>
At least 853,764 persons have been affected by floods in 816
villages in Pampanga, Bataan, Zambales, Bulacan, Tarlac and Nueva
Ecija, the office said.
</P>
<P>
Torrential rains from Monday to Wednesday in Central Luzon and
the Philippine capital of Manila caused massive floods. In Manila,
at least 10 people were killed in the disaster and thousands were
evacuated from lower parts of the city.  
</P>
</TEXT>
