<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rafter Ousts Chang at Hamlet Cup Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Australian Patrick Rafter
ousted top seed Michael Chang Friday night at the quarter-finals
of the Hamlet Cup at Commack, New York.
</P>
<P>
The eighth-seeded Rafter, who was ranked 14th in world, beat
world number two American Chang 6-4, 3-6, 6-1 in his warmup for
the U.S. Open starting next week.
</P>
<P>
Chang broke Rafter in the first game of their third set but
lost his own serve for a 1-1 tie. In the fourth game, Chang hit a
forehand long that allowed Rafter to overtake the lead 3-1.
</P>
<P>
In his next service game, Chang was down 0-40 but a Rafter
backhand error, a 146-kph ace and a stellar Chang forehand
crosscourt passing shot took it to deuce. Rafter used a forehand
half-volley to finally break for 5-1.
</P>
<P>
Rafter was down 15-40 while serving for the match, but Chang
mis-hit into the stands for 30-40 and was forced to opposite sides
of the court for three difficult retrievals with his third return
wide.
</P>
<P>
Rafter put the seal on the point by using his forehead to knock
home the high-bouncing ball for a "winner" into the open court.
</P>
<P>
After Chang blasted a forehand long, Rafter closed out the
match with a 145-kph ace.
</P>
<P>
Rafter improved his lifetime record against Chang to 2-5. The
two will meet again next month when the United States hosts
Australia in a Davis Cup semifinal in Washington.
</P>
<P>
Chang has never won the Hamlet Cup, despite playing it for five
of the past six years with the absence in 1995. He has been a
quarter-finalist all five years and advanced to the semis in 1992
and the final in 1993 where he lost to Marc Rosset.
</P>
<P>
In the semifinals, Rafter will face Sweden's Thomas Enqvist,
who defeated Germany's Marc-Kevin Goellner 6-4, 6-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
