that the Israelis want to pay homage to the spot where their
soldiers freed 102 hostages from a plane hijacked by Palestinians
in 1976.
</P>
<P>
He said Entebbe will raise money from tourists on completion
of the center.
</P>
<P>
The old airport terminal building will be preserved as it is,
while more structures will be put up to house shopping malls,
restaurant and other facilities, Muzoora said.
</P>
<P>
Ashkelon city, which twinned with Entebbe Municipal Council in
1994 will also help the council construct a town hall.
</P>
<P>
Ashkelon has also given the council two university
scholarships each year, he added. 
