<HEADLINE> Dead Nepalese Boy Still Bleeds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 23 (Xinhua) -- A Nepalese boy who was
declared dead from insect bites, was still bleeding for four days,
local newspaper The Kathmandu Post reported today.
</P>
<P>
The 13-year-old boy in Saptari district of eastern Nepal was
sleeping with another boy in the same room when they were bitten
by unknown insects.
</P>
<P>
The boy died instantly and the other has recovered after
treatment at hospital, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
His relatives did not allow the body to be cremated because it
was bleeding.
</P>
<P>
It was strange that after two days, the cuts at the ear and
finger of the boy were still bleeding and the body was not
stinking.
</P>
<P>
And no change appeared in the shape of the dead body, the paper
said quoting witnesses.
</P>
<P>
"People insisted that it was a case of witchcraft and as there
is no legal provision of it, I requested the relatives to have it
cremated," said Mayor Jagar Das Las.
</P>
<P>
Later, the body was put in a river with name and address on it,
the paper said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
