<HEADLINE> Floods Hit Southern Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Heavy floods hit six provinces
in southern Thailand as tropical storm Cida swept the region
Friday, causing damages to property, farmland and crops.
</P>
<P>
Chumphon province was hit hardest by the storm which brought
widespread downpours to the region, local newspapers said today.
</P>
<P>
Floodwaters and mudslides damaged roads and bridges and 67
villages and 2,988 families were affected in the province.
</P>
<P>
In neighboring Ranong province, some 560 hectares of
agricultural land in its two districts bordering Chumphon province
were flooded and 670 families were evacuated.
</P>
<P>
Trang province and Satun province were also affected by the
storm.
</P>
<P>
So far, no death was reported due to the flooding in the
region. 
</P>
