<HEADLINE> World's Top Shuttler Dong Upset in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Budding star Indra Wijaya of
Indonesia scored a victory on Friday, upsetting world's top
shuttler Dong Jiong of China 13-15, 15-12, 15-13 in the World Cup
Badminton Championship in Yogyakarta.
</P>
<P>
In another surprise, Ong Ewe Hock of Malaysia eliminated
Indonesia's Haryanto Arbi with an easy win of 15-0, 15-5.
</P>
<P>
Trailing 14-9 in the opening set, Wijaya caught up before Jiong
sealed the first set 15-13 and Dong seemed to savor his victory as
he led 12-6 in the second set.
</P>
<P>
But Wijaya rallied back to win nine points in a row without
allowing a single point for Jiong.
</P>
<P>
In the decider set, Dong rushed ahead again 12-7 but lost his
stamina as the Indonesian forced back under the cheers of the home
fans.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Sun Jun made it to the best-four round by beating Soren
Nielsen of Denmark, 15-5, 15-1.
</P>
<P>
Sun Jun, the world's no. 2 shuttler, will face Hock while
Wijaya will take on compatriot Joko Suprianto.
</P>
<P>
In the women's singles, the host Indonesia and China exchanged
victories as Indonesian Susi Susanti disposed off Wang Chen, while
top-seeded Ye Zhaoying eliminated Meiluawati 9-11, 11-3, 11-2.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Susant will play another Chinese Gong
Zhichao, and Ye will be challenged by Indonesian Mia Audiana.
</P>
<P>
Both Gong and Audina had already secured the semifinal berth
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In the women's doubles, the Chinese shuttlers dominated the
competition with Gei Fei and Gu Jun outclassing Indarti Isolina
and Finarsih 15-6, 15-2, and Qin Yiyuan and Tang Songshu beating
Eliza and Zelin Rosiana 15-12, 11-15, 15-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
