<HEADLINE> Housing Funds Grow in Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Chile's Housing Funds
Administrators System has accumulated 20 million U.S. dollars
since it started operation in May 1995, the Housing and
Urbanization Ministry said here today.
</P>
<P>
This was an expansion of nearly 56 percent since last December
and a 210 percent increase over 12 months.
</P>
<P>
The system comprises four private housing funds administrating
firms in the country, and it had 97,066 title holders in July.
</P>
<P>
Chile built 139,000 housing units last year, but there was
still a demand for another 500,000.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean government plans to gradually solve its housing
problem through measures including the Housing Funds system.
</P>
</TEXT>
