<HEADLINE> United States Beats Domincian Republic in Basketball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The United States scored a
comfortable win over the Dominican Republic 98-70 in a qualifying
match here on Friday for the 1998 basketball World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
The American cagers never looked in danger as Jason Sasser
paced the squad with 31 points through his accurate long-distance
shots.
</P>
<P>
The United States which enjoyed an advantage of 49-38 at half
break, was the automatic qualifier for the World Cup as reigning
world champions.
</P>
<P>
For the Dominican Republic, Carlos Martinez was the leading
scorer with 21 points, but he failed to stop his teammates to lose
the second straight match afer going down 88-85 against Puerto
Rico on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Later Friday, Cuba overturned a halftime deficit of 40-36 to
defeat Mexico 71-68. Cuba's Lazaro Borrell was top scorer with 19
points, followed by Mexico's Enrique Gonzalez with 17.
</P>
<P>
The tournament has a 10-team field with the top four qualifying
for the zone's berths in the 1998 World Championships. 
