<HEADLINE> Medical Devices to Steal Spotlight of Exports Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Beijing enterprises producing
medical devices will get a prominent share of the spotlight in the
coming 82nd China Export Commodities Fair, a biannual grand event
in Guangzhou, today's "China Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
five well-established enterprises of that type will compose a
delegation to demonstrate one cutting-edge aspect of Beijing's
high-tech industry, said Xu Xiaoxi, director of the Beijing
Commission of Foreign Trade and Economic Co-operation.
</P>
<P>
The move was proposed after the first Beijing computer group,
composed of several Beijing computer giants such as Founder, Stone
and legend, garnered numerous orders at the fair, Xu said.
</P>
<P>
She said that this year, the commission would set the medical
and computer groups as the most notable in the 60-member Beijing
delegation.
</P>
<P>
With the 10 booths and a product briefing conference during the
fair, the five medical device-producing enterprises will show
their key products to business people from all over the world, Xu
said.
</P>
<P>
The products include X-ray examination system, economical CT
scanners, accelerator, computerized breast-scan diagnosing
apparatuses and telephone-transmission ECG (electrocardiograph)
monitoring systems.
</P>
<P>
Exports of medical devices make up only a tiny portion of
China's annual four billion US dollars worth of exports of medical
products, said Zhao Chunhua, president of China chamber of
commerce of medicine and health product importers and exporters.
</P>
<P>
He said Beijing, with its high-tech advantages, boasts the
largest sales volume in each year's spring and autumn national
exhibitions of medical devices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
