<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Capital Firm Reports Solid Profits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Yanhua Petrochemical Co
Ltd. reported a relatively satisfactory performance for the first
half year despite the sluggish domestic market, and released huge
expansion plans, today's "China Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
The company's H shares become listed on the New York Stock
Exchange and on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange in June this
year. The stock issue has brought the firm 232 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Liu Haiyan, chairman of the company, said the firm's production
sales during the first half year reached 2.9 billion yuan (349
million US dollars), up 5.3 percent from the same period of last
year.
</P>
<P>
Profits before tax and net profit for the period were 449
million yuan (54 million US dollars) and 300 million yuan (36
million US dollars) respectively, 17.3 percent and 6.2 percent
more than that of the first half year of 1996. Earnings per share
amounted to 0.13 yuan.
</P>
<P>
He said the performance was satisfactory, taking into account
the weak global petrochemical market and declining product prices
during the period. He attributed the growth to improved product
mix and enhanced operating efficiency.
</P>
<P>
Sales of higher value-added products of the firm during the
first half year almost doubled that of the corresponding period
last year, and the company developed nine new specialized resins
and plastics products, he said. Meanwhile, selling and
administrative spending declined by 10.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Liu said: "I'm confident that we can achieve the net profit
target of 684 million yuan this year.
</P>
<P>
He said the firm is to launch a big ethylene project, which
will expand its ethylene production capacity from 450,000 tons to
660,000 tons. The project is expected to gain formal approval from
related authorities in the near future, he said.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Yanhua is the largest producer of resins and plastics
in China, and one of the largest producers of ethylene of the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
