<HEADLINE> Alonso Beats Ivanisevic at New York Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Qualifier Julian Alonso of
Spain beat second seed and world number four Goran Ivanisevic of
Croatia 7-6 (7-4), 3-6, 6-3 at the Hamlet Cup tennis tournament at
Commack, New York on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Alonso, ranked 76th in the world, had an ace of 225 kilometers
per hour to score the first point of the ninth game in the first
set of their quarter-final match.
</P>
<P>
He thus became one of the fastest men in ATP Tour history in
their serves, so far only three tennis players had achieved the
greatest feat.
</P>
<P>
The record is held by Australia's Mark Philippoussis at 229
kph, while Britain's Greg Rusedski reached 225 mph earlier this
month in New Haven.
</P>
<P>
The Hamlet Cup is Alonso's second ATP Tour event. The Lipton in
Florida was the first, where he beat Britain's Tim Henman before
going out in the third round.
</P>
<P>
Alonso will meet countryman Carlos Moya in Saturday's
semifinals. Moya beat Germany's Marc-Kevin Goellner 6-4, 6-4 in an
earlier quarter-finals, and Sweden's Thomas Enqvist defeated
Germany's Marc-Kevin Goellner 6-4, 6-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
