<HEADLINE> 34 Schemes Planned for Developing Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Colombo, August (Xinhua) -- A total of 34 schemes have been
drawn up to develop Jaffna city in northern Sri Lanka, according
to reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
These schemes were worked out by the United Nations Development
Program (UNDP) in collaboration with the government agent in
Jaffna city and the Jaffna rehabilitation and Resettlement
Authority.
</P>
<P>
Of the sum, 14 schemes will be implemented soon, including
technical education, animal husbandry, highway repairs,
agriculture, fishing and self-employment projects for women and
school leavers.
</P>
<P>
The reports said the Agricultural School at Thirunelvely will
be reorganized and made to function again.
</P>
<P>
The National Youth Services Council in Jaffna will be assisted
by the UNDP in the training of school leavers in vocational
studies, English language and self-employment, the reports noted.
</P>
<P>
Goat rearing is another scheme that will be undertaken by the
school leavers, said the reports, adding that goats of pure breed
will be obtained from India.
</P>
<P>
Jaffna city was once the stronghold of the Tamil rebels who
have been fighting a guerrilla war for a separate state in the
north and east of the country since 1983. Government troops
recaptured Jaffna Peninsula in May last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
