<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Baht Dives to Record Low Against U.S. Dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's currency baht Friday
further weakened, plunging to a record low on the local market as
the baht quoted at some commercial banks once exceeded 34 baht to
the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
The baht was traded at 33.25 to 34.05 against the dollar at
other local commercial banks, although the reference rate quoted
by the Thai Central Bank stood at 32.68.
</P>
<P>
The baht also was once traded at 34.10 to 34.30 against the
dollars at other commercial banks Friday, local newspapers said.
</P>
<P>
The plunge was due to the recent disclosure by the Thai Central
Bank that it faced an outstanding currency forward obligations
totaling 23.4 billion dollars over the next 12 years.
</P>
<P>
The announcement of the Central Bank will further dampen
investors' sentiment and the baht is expected to drop lower to 35
against the dollar in coming days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
