<HEADLINE> Testud Faces Davenport in Atlanta Tennis Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Unseeded Sandrine Testud of
France beat third seed and French Open champion Iva Majoli of
Croatia 7-5, 6-3 on Friday to meet fourth-seeded American Lindsay
Davenport in Saturday's final of the 450,000 U.S. dollar U.S.
Women's Hardcourt Championships in Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
It was Testud's second WTA Tour final this year. Testud who
has improved to 38-17 this year, captured her first career WTA
Tour title last month by winning the International Tournament in
Palermo, Italy.
</P>
<P>
Testud, ranked 18th in the world, entered the semifinal
Thursday after second seed Monica Seles of the United States was
forced to withdraw due to a high fever and throat virus.
</P>
<P>
Majoli was appearing in her sixth semifinal this season and was
seeking her first final following her victory in the French
Open. She saw her 1997 record fall to 40-16.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Davenport eliminated fifth seed Amanda Coetzer of
South Africa 6-2, 6-4 Friday night.
</P>
<P>
Davenport has won five of seven lifetime meetings with Coetzer,
including a straight-set victory in Amelia Island, Florida,
earlier this year en route to the title. 
</P>
</TEXT>
