<HEADLINE> Honduran Army Officers Sue Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEGUCIGALPA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- A group of officers of the
Honduran armed forces filed a lawsuit against the government for
refusing to paying for their services in the Western Sahara Desert
in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The officers demanded a government payment of 200,000
U.S. dollars in the case to cover their travel and other expenses
incurred when they served in the African region.
</P>
<P>
Honduras sent them at a UN request to the region on a peace
mission last year.
</P>
<P>
Some 120 Honduran soldiers had participated in the mission and
all of them did not receive the promised payment.
</P>
<P>
The officers said they will try all they can to to get the
payment. 
