<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Clean Tourist Section of Great Wall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The Badaling Special Zone has
launched a two- to Three-year comprehensive program for the
protection of this most visited section of the Great Wall in the
northern outskirts of the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
The program includes two major projects, a Badaling
International Friendship Forest and a culture square around the
area, which averages more than 20,000 visitors a day, today's
China Daily reports.
</P>
<P>
According to the protection program, a culture square will be
built at the foot of the wall, where a market street and a parking
area now exist. The latter two have been attacked as distorting
the natural appearance of this section of the Great Wall.
</P>
<P>
The future square is suggested to contain an ancient-style
battlefield, statues of the famous people relating to the wall's
history and a forest of steles.
</P>
<P>
The scattered markets in the Badaling area will then be
concentrated into one trade center.
</P>
<P>
After a highway is completed late this year, the current
parking area will be removed and vehicles forbidden inside the
scenic spot, the paper quoted an official of the zone agency as
saying.
</P>
<P>
At present there is only one road running through the scenic
spot, and all vehicles pass directly through the Great Wall
gateway.
</P>
<P>
According to the three-year blueprint, a more than 40 sq km
barren hill area along the west edge of the Badaling Great Wall
will be transformed into a forest park, with a man-made waterfall,
gardens and many other landscapes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
