<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazilian Forces To Replace U.S. Troops in MOMEP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian forces will replace the
U.S. troops in the Group of Logistical Support of the Ecuador-Peru
Military Observers Mission (MOMEP) in December, a spokesman for
the group said today.
</P>
<P>
The technical meeting of the guarantor countries held recently
in Brasilia approved the plan to substitute the support group formed
by the four guarantor countries -- Argentina, Brazil, Chile and
the United States.
</P>
<P>
A MOMEP official said that the Brazilian personnel will start
arriving in October and hangars are under construction for
Brazilian helicopters, which will be used to watch the security
zone.
</P>
<P>
He said that four helicopters will fly in on November 2 to
replace U.S. helicopters.
</P>
<P>
Six Argentine officers will be in charge of the MOMEP personnel
management and seven Chileans responsible for health care while 20
Americans will continue to take care of communication, meteorology
and liaison for logistical flights, the MOMEP official said.
</P>
<P>
By December 20, the MOMEP will have 115 men, 39 of whom are
military observers and 76 are of the logistical support group.
</P>
</TEXT>
