<HEADLINE> Italian Wins Men's 400m Freestyle in European Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Italy's Emiliano Brembilla beat
the rainy weather to win the men's 400 meters freestyle at the
European Swimming Championships in Seville on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Italian destroyed Paul Palmer's hope of a third gold in the
pool when he overtook the pace-setter Briton at midway and touched
home first with a margin of more than two seconds against fellow
Massimiliano Rosolino.
</P>
<P>
Palmer was third after winning Tuesday's 200 meters freestyle
and pacing Britain to victory in Wednesday's 4x200 meters
freestyle relay.
</P>
<P>
The 18-year-old Brembilla clocked three minutes 45.96 seconds,
the third-fastest mark in the event of all time.
</P>
<P>
Rosolino, who finished second behind Palmer in the 200 meters
freestyle, took another silver in 3:48.11 and Palmer the bronze in
3:50.03.
</P>
<P>
Double Olympic champion Alexander Popov led Russia to victory
in the men's 4x100 meters freestyle relay in a European record
time of 3:16.85, overpassing the previous mark of 3:17.06 set in
the Atlanta Olympics last July.
</P>
<P>
Denmark's Mette Jacobsen retained her European 100 meters
butterfly title in 59.64, beating Slovakia's Martina Moravcova to
second by a tenth of a second.
</P>
<P>
Alexander Goukov of Belarus and Agnes Kovacs of Hungary both
celebrated their breaststroke doubles.
</P>
<P>
Goukov came from fourth at halfway to beat pace-setter Russian
Andrei Korneyev in the last length, adding the men's 200 meters
breaststroke crown to the 100 meters he won on Tuesday. Goukov
won in 2:13.90, half a second ahead of Korneyev.
</P>
<P>
Kovacs, who broke her own European record in the women's 200
meters breaststroke on Wednesday, took her second European crown
from 1995 double champion Brigitte Becue of Belgium by winning the
100 meters in 1:08.08.
</P>
<P>
Becue had to settle for her second bronze as the silver medal
was stolen by Svitlana Bondarenko of Ukraine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
