<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuba Has Links with 160 Countries Despite U.S. Embargo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Cuba has established links with
160 countries and absorbed a great amount of foreign investment
despite the long-term United States economic embargo, the official
Granma Daily said here today.
</P>
<P>
"Cuba is blocked but it is not isolated," said the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The country has opened 85 embassies in the world, a
considerable increase over the 30 in the pre-revolutionary year of
1959, it noted.
</P>
<P>
More than 20 countries established relations with the island
country after 1993 when an economic crisis, mainly caused by the
disintegration of the former Soviet Union, hit Cuba, it added.
</P>
<P>
Besides the establishment of foreign ties with many countries,
Cuba also gained permanent representation in many international
organizations, it said.
</P>
<P>
It had experienced unceasing increases in foreign investment
and in the number of foreign tourists. More than one million
foreign tourists visited the country last year.
</P>
<P>
The 14th World Festival of Youth and Students, which was held
in Cuba recently with the attendance of 12,000 foreign guests,
demonstrated the solidarity between Cuba and the world, said
the newspaper. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970823.0218 </DOCNO>
