<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items
in leading Philippine newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Manila Bulletin
</P>
<P>
-- The Philippine government said Friday that the country's
sugar tariff will definitely go down to zero to 5 percent
effective 2004 in line with the ASEAN's timetable for a uniform
tariff level.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Journal
</P>
<P>
-- The "El Nino" phenomenon will reduce the Philippines' crop
production late this year and in the first half of 1988, the
Agriculture Department admitted Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Manila Standard
</P>
<P>
-- Senators Friday urged President Fidel Ramos to heed the
warning of Cardinal Sin that there will be civil strife if the
administration insists on pushing its plan to lift term limits of
elective officials by convening the congress into a constituent
assembly.
</P>
<P>
The Manila Chronicle
</P>
<P>
-- Lower demand for dollars as Philippine exporters decided to
unload their greenback holdings caused the peso to appreciate
further Friday from 29.97 pesos against the dollar to 29.85 pesos.
</P>
