<HEADLINE> Testud Upsets Majoli to Advance to WTA Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Unseeded Sandrine Testud of
France beat third seed and French Open champion Iva Majoli of
Croatia 7-5, 6-3 on Friday to enter the final of the 450,000 U.S.
dollar U.S. Women's Hardcourt Championships held at Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old Testud, ranked 18th in the world, will take on
the winner of tonight's second semifinal pitting fourth seed
Lindsay Davenport of the United States and fifth seed Amanda
Coetzer of South Africa.
</P>
<P>
It was Testud's second WTA Tour final this year. Testud who
has improved to 38-17 this year, captured her first career WTA
Tour title last month by winning the International Tournament in
Palermo, Italy.
</P>
<P>
Testud entered the semifinal Thursday after second seed Monica
Seles of the United States was forced to withdraw due to a high
fever and throat virus. 
</P>
</TEXT>
