<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hungary, Russia Join Gold Medal Winners at Universiade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Russia and Hungary joined
the gold medal winners at the 19th World University Games by taking
one gold each here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Hungary's gold came from women's individual epee as Timea Nagy beat
Karina Aznavourian of Russia 15-13 in the finals.
</P>
<P>
Russia took the women's gymnastics team event with a total of
110.537 points. The United States snatched the silver medal at 108.986
points, followed by Japan in the third place with a total of 108.624
points.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese women's team, consisting of young and unexperienced
gymnasts, had a slow start in their first event of vault and finished
only fouth at 108.362 points.
</P>
<P>
In the fencing competition, Nagy is the brightest star on Friday.
She put up a steady performance and sailed all the way into the final.
</P>
<P>
Her rival in the final was Karina Aznavourian of Russia. Nagy was
more aggressive and quicker than Aznavourian. After an exciting
battle, Nagy finally edged Aznavourian 15-13 for the title.
</P>
<P>
The level of the women's epee competitions were so high that Cuba's
gold and silver medalists at last month's world championships at Cape
Town were eliminated before the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
Yang Shaoqi, a World Cup winner from China, finished only sixth in
the event. She said that she was not physically strong enough to
follow the pace of her rival and that explained her early exit from
the competitions.
</P>
<P>
The group competitions of the football tournament ended at Palermo
today with eight teams from four groups qualifying for the second
round.
</P>
<P>
China, the first team to be ensured of a berth in the second round,
lost 3-1 to the United States. The American team finished as the
winners of the group which also includes Nigeria and Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
Hosts Italy scored their second victory, beating Britain 3-1 and
also advanced into the second round. The other qualifiers from group
A are the Brazilians who beat Iran 5-1.
</P>
<P>
In group B, Ireland edged Japan by better goal difference to finish
as runners-up. Ukraine won the group with 5 points.
</P>
<P>
The group C saw the Netherlands and South Korea advance into the
next round. The two teams fought to a 1-1 draw to garner 5 points
each. South Africa and Uruguay were eliminated from the competitions.
</P>
<P>
The tennis tournament continued at Palermo on Friday. The men's
top-seeded player Yoog Yong Il of South Korea sailed into the third
round after beating Pablo Contardo of Chile.
</P>
<P>
The women's top-seed Wang Shi-Ting also entered the last 16 with a
6-4, 6-2 victory over Ding Ding of China.
</P>
<P>
The Universiade continued on Saturday with fencing, gymnastics,
volleyball, basketball and tennis. 
</P>
